post.description:
This endpoint provides the ability to retrieve rate quotes and optionalll transit information. The rate is calculated based on the origin and destination of the shipment. Additional information such as carrier code, service type, or service option can be used to filter the results. If carrier code is provided, the response includes the rate quotes for the specific transportation carrier. This endpoint provides the rates for FedEx Ground and FedEx Express and does not offer rates for FedEx Freight.
Note: FedEx APIs do not support Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) mechanism.

x-code-samples.source:
<?php

$request = new HttpRequest();
$request->setUrl('https://apis-sandbox.fedex.com/rate/v1/rates/quotes');
$request->setMethod(HTTP_METH_POST);

$request->setHeaders(array(
  'Authorization' => 'Bearer ',
  'X-locale' => 'en_US',
  'Content-Type' => 'application/json'
));

$request->setBody(input); // 'input' refers to JSON Payload

try {
  $response = $request->send();

  echo $response->getBody();
} catch (HttpException $ex) {
  echo $ex;
}

import requests

url = "https://apis-sandbox.fedex.com/rate/v1/rates/quotes"

payload = input # 'input' refers to JSON Payload
headers = {
    'Content-Type': "application/json",
    'X-locale': "en_US",
    'Authorization': "Bearer "
    }

response = requests.post(url, data=payload, headers=headers)

print(response.text)

customerMessages.description:
These are messages concerning the ability to provide an accurate delivery commitment on an International commit quote. These could be providing information about why a commitment could not be returned or a successful message
Example:
  • REQUEST_COMPLETED
    Request completed successfully
  • SERVICE.TYPE.INTERNATIONAL.MESSAGE:
    Rate does not include duties & taxes, clearance entry fees or other import fees. The payor of duties/taxes/fees will be responsible for any applicable Clearance Entry Fees.
  • NATIONAL.HOLIDAY.OBSERVED:
    National Holiday Observed on Ship Date.
  • INCONSISTENT.COMMODITY.DESCRIPTION:
    The description and harmonized code for the specified commodity are not consistent.

harmonizedCode.description:
This is to specify the Harmonized Tariff System (HTS) code to meet U.S. and foreign governments' customs requirements. These are mainly used to estimate the duties and taxes.
Example: A six digit code for Almonds fresh or dried is 080211. The HTS code for pistachios in shell is 080251. The HTS code for fish is HS203.
To research the classification for your commodity, use the FedEx Global Trade Manager online at fedex.com/gtm. You can find the commodities and its respective codes by logging into FedEx and selecting harmonized code option. You will find country-specific information to determine whether your commodity is considered to be a document or non-document for your destination.
For additional information about harmonized code, refer to harmonized code.

alternativeCommodityNames.description: Specifies the alternate names of commodities.

label.description:

Example: Deliverydate unavailable

commitMessageDetails.description:
Messages concerning the ability to provide an accurate delivery commitment on an International commit quote. These could be messages providing information about why a commitment could not be returned or a successful message.
Example: Message

commodityName.description:
The Commodity applicable to this commitment.
Example: DOCUMENTS

dayOfWeek.description:
specific day of week in short format
Example: MON, TUE

dayFormat.description:
This is expected delivery date in format [YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss]
Example: 2020-07-16T10:30:00

DateDetail.description: These are date and time details.

dayOfWeek.description: The delay day of the week

level.description: The attribute of the shipment that caused the delay(e.g. Country, City, LocationId, Zip, service area, special handling)

point.description: The point in transit where the delay is occurring (e.g. Origin, Destination, Broker location)

type.description: The reason for the delay (e.g. holiday, weekend, etc.).

description.description: The name of the holiday in that country that is causing the delay.

DelayDetail.description: Information about why a shipment delivery is delayed and at what level

TransitDays.description: These are number of days the package/shipment is to be in transit. Applies to Ground and LTL Freight; indicates minimum transit time for SmartPost.

description.description:
Specifies the number of days the package/shipment is to be in transit.
Example: 2 Business Days

minimumTransitTime.description:
Code indicating the number of transit days.
Example: TW0_DAYS

smartPostIndiciaType.description: This identifies the indicia used during rate quote.

ServiceSubOptionDetail.description: These are supporting detail for applied options identified in a rate quote.

Example: AnyCo_order123456789

processingOptions.description: Array of processing options for the shipment.

carrierCodes.description:
Specify the four letter code of a FedEx operating company that meets your requirements.
Example: FDXE
  • FDXE - FedEx Express
  • FDXG - FedEx Ground
  • FXSP - FedEx SmartPost
  • FXCC - FedEx Custom Critical.

Full_Schema_Quote_Rate.description: The request elements for requesting a rate quote.

major.description: This version is incremented when significant changes are made to the API functionality. These could be breaking changes and might require code-adjustments from clients. Accepts only numbers

minor.description: This represents a backward-compatible bug fix or minor adjustment to an existing API functionality. This is the second number in API versioning scheme. Accepts only numbers

patch.description: This represents a backward-compatible bug fix or minor adjustment to an existing API functionality. This is the third number in API versioning scheme. Accepts only numbers

returnTransitTimes.description:
Indicate if the transit time and commit data are to be returned in the reply. Default value is false.
Valid values are TRUE and FALSE.

servicesNeededOnRateFailure.description:
Specify the services to be requested if the rate data is not available.
Valid values are TRUE and FALSE.

variableOptions.description:
Specify service options whose combinations are to be considered when replying with available services.
Example: FREIGHT_GUARANTEE

rateSortOrder.description:
This is a sort order you can specify to control the order of the response data.
Example: SERVICENAMETRADITIONAL

  • SERVICENAMETRADITIONAL - data in order of highest to lowest service (Default)
  • COMMITASCENDING - data in order of ascending delivery committment
  • COMMITDESCENDING - data in order of descending delivery committment.

RateRequestControlParameters.description: Specify the return transit times, services needed on rate failure, choice of variable option and order to sort rate options to filter and sort the expected response.

shipper.description: The descriptive data for the physical shipper location from which the shipment originates.

recipient.description: Indicate the descriptive data for the recipient location to which the shipment is to be received.

serviceType.description:
Indicate the FedEx service type used for this shipment. The results will be filtered by the service type value indicated. If no serviceType is indicated then all the applicable services and corresponding rates will be returned.
Example: STANDARD_OVERNIGHT
Click here to see Service Types

preferredCurrency.description:
Indicate the currency the caller requests to have used in all returned monetary values (when a choice is possible). Used in conjunction with the rateRequestType data element. This element is used to pull Preferred rates.
Example: USD
Click here to see Currency Codes

rateRequestType.description:
Indicate the type of rates to be returned.
Following are values:
  • LIST - Returns FedEx published list rates in addition to account-specific rates (if applicable).
  • PREFERRED - Returns rates in the preferred currency specified in the element preferredCurrency.
  • ACCOUNT - Returns account specific rates (Default).
  • INCENTIVE - This is one-time discount for incentivising the customer. For more information, contact your FedEx representative.
Examples: ["LIST","PREFERRED"]

shipDateStamp.description:
This is shipment date. Both the date and time portions of the string are expected to be used. The date should not be a past date or a date more than 10 days in the future. The time is the local time of the shipment based on the shipper's time zone.
Required Format is YYYY-MM-DD
Example: 2019-09-05

pickupType.description:
Indicate the pickup type method by which the shipment to be tendered to FedEx.
Click here for more information on Pickup Types.

requestedPackageLineItems.description:
These are one or more package-attribute descriptions, each of which describes an individual package, a group of identical packages, or (for the total-piece-total-weight case) common characteristics of all packages in the shipment.
  • At least one instance containing the weight for at least one package is required for EXPRESS and GROUND shipments.
  • Not used for FREIGHT.
  • Single piece requests will have one RequestedPackageLineItem.
  • Multiple piece requests will have multiple RequestedPackageLineItems.
  • Maximum occurrences is 99.

documentShipment.description: Indicate whether or not its a document Shipment.

variableHandlingChargeDetail.description: contains the detail used to calculate a variable handling charge, a potentially non-fixed handling surcharge. Based on if there is a percent value, or a fixed amount, the charge can either be fixed or percents based.

packagingType.description:
This is the Packaging type associated with this rate. For Ground/SmartPost,it will always be YOUR_PACKAGING. For domestic Express, the packaging may have been bumped so it may not match the value specified on the request. For International Express the packaging may be bumped and not mapped.
Click here to see Package Types

totalPackageCount.description:
Indicate the total number of packages in the shipment.
The Maximum number of packages in a rate request is 100.

totalWeight.description:
Specify the total weight of the shipment.
This is only applies to International shipments and should be used on the first package of a multiple piece shipment. This value contains 1 explicit decimal position.

RequestedShipment.description: This is shipment data for which a rate quote (or rate-shipping comparison) is requested.

RateAddress.description: Descriptive data for a physical location. May be used as an actual physical address (place to which one could go), or as a container of address parts which should be handled as a unit (such as a city-state-ZIP combination within  the US). Country code is required.  Postal code is required for postal aware countries.

city.description:
This is a placeholder for City Name.
Example: Beverly Hills

stateOrProvinceCode.description:
This is a placeholder for State or Province code. State code is required for US, CA, PR and not required for other countries. Conditional. Max length is 2 .
Example: CA
Click here to see State Or Province Code

postalCode.description:
Indicate the Postal code. This is optional for non postal-aware countries. Maximum length is 10.
Example: 65247
Click here to see Postal aware countries

countryCode.description:
This is the two-letter country code. Maximum length is 2.
Example: US
Click here to see Country Codes

residential.description: Indicate whether this address is residential (as opposed to commercial).

Address_2.description: This is detailed information on physical location. May be used as an actual physical address (place to which one could go), or as a container of address parts which should be handled as a unit (such as a city-state-ZIP combination within the U.S.).

emailAddress.description: Identifies the email address associated with this contact.

notificationType.description: Specifies the type of the notification received.

locale.description:
Specify the locale details.
Example: 'en_US'
Click here to see the list of available locales

Note: If the locale is left blank or an invalid locale is entered, an error message is returned in response.

EmailNotificationRecipient.description: Data specifying the recipient(s) of notifications related to the movement of the shipment. At a minimnum an EmailnotificationRecipientType, at least one NoficationEventType, and an EmailAddress are required.

SmsDetail.description:
Specifies the SMS notification details.
Conditionally required for SMS notifications.

subPackagingType.description:
This is a physical packaging type used for the package.
Click here to see sub-packaging types
For more information on physical packaging or packaging regulatory requirements, visit fedex.com or contact your FedEx representative.

groupPackageCount.description:
Indicate the grouped package count. These are number of identical package(s) each with one or more commodities.
Example: 2

declaredValue.description: This is the Declared Value - represents FedEx Maximum liability in connection with a shipment of that Package, including but not limited to, any loss, damage, delay, misdelivery, any failure to provide information, or misdelivery of information relating to the Shipment.

weight.description: Indicate the total weight of the requested package line items.

packageSpecialServices.description: These special services are available at the package level for some or all service types.  Indicated if rate data is being requested for the special services.

amount.description: Indicates the declared amount value for the shipment.

currency.description: Indicates the currency associated with the amount.

Indicate the three-character ISO currency code.
Example: USD
Click here to see Currency Codes

Money_1.description: Indicate the amount details. This is optional, but if indicated, amount and currency must be provided.

units.description: Specifies the package weight unit. For Dry Ice the unit of measure is KG.

batteryMaterialType.description: Describes the material composition of the battery or cell.

RequestePackageLineItemDimensions.description: Specify the dimensions of this package and the unit type used for the measurements. Valid measurements are whole numbers greater than zero.

Dimensions.description:
Indicate the dimensions of the package.
Following conditions will apply:
  • Dimensions are optional but when added, then all three dimensions must be indicated.
  • Dimensions are required with YOUR_PACKAGING package type.
Note: The Maximum/minimum dimension values varies based on the services and the packaging types. Refer FedEx Service Guide for service details related to DIM Weighting for FedEx Express and oversize conditions for FedEx Express and FedEx Ground.

length.description:
Indicate the length of the package. No implied decimal places. Maximum value: 999
Example: 20

width.description:
Indicate the width of the package. No implied decimal places. Maximum value: 999
Example: 10

height.description:
Indicate the height of the package. No implied decimal places. Maximum value: 999
Example: 10

units.description:
Indicate the unit of measure for the provided dimensions.
Valid Values are:
  • IN - Inches
  • CM - Centimeters

length.description:
Indicate the length of the package. No implied decimal places. Maximum value: 999
Example: 20

width.description:
Indicate the width of the package. No implied decimal places. Maximum value: 999
Example: 10

height.description:
Indicate the height of the package. No implied decimal places. Maximum value: 999
Example: 10

units.description:
Indicate the unit of measure for the provided dimensions.
Valid Values are:
  • IN - Inches
  • CM - Centimeters

Dimensions_1.description:

Following conditions will apply:
  • Dimensions are optional but when added, then all three dimensions must be indicated.
  • Dimensions are required with YOUR_PACKAGING package type.
Note: The Maximum/minimum dimension values varies based on the services and the packaging types. Refer FedEx Service Guide for service details related to DIM Weighting for FedEx Express and oversize conditions for FedEx Express and FedEx Ground.

rateType.description: The rate type indicates what type of rate request is being returned; account, preferred, incentive, etc.

percentValue.description: Indicate the variable handling percentage. Actual percentage (10 means 10%, which is a mutiplier of 0.1).

rateLevelType.description: indicates whether or not the rating is being done at the package level, or if the packages are bundled together. At the package level, charges are applied based on the details of each individual package. If they are bundled, one package is chosen as the parent and charges are applied based on that one package.

fixedValue.description:
Indicate the Fixed value.
If you choose FIXED_AMOUNT as the ChargeType, this element allows you to enter the fixed value of the handling charge. The element allows entry of 7 characters before the decimal and 2 characters following the decimal.
Example - 5.00.

rateElementBasis.description: Indicate the rate charge on which, the variable handling amount is calculated.

VariableHandlingChargeDetail.description: Indicate the details on how to calculate variable handling charges at the package level. If indicated, element rateLevelType is required.

specialServiceTypes.description:
Indicate the special services requested.
Click here to see Package level Special Service Types

pieceCountVerificationBoxCount.description: Provide the pieceCount or VerificationBoxCount for batteries or cells that are contained within this specific package.

batteryDetails.description: Specify the details about the batteries or cells that are contained within this specific package.

standaloneBatteryDetails.description: Provides details about the batteries or cells that are contained within this specific package.

PackageSpecialServicesRequested.description: These special services are available at the package level for some or all service types. Needs Indicated, if rate data is being requested for the special services.

alcoholRecipientType.description: Specify the recipient type for the alcohol shipment.

shipperAgreementType.description:
Specify the shipper entity type.
Example: Fulfillment house, Retailer or a Winery.

AlcoholDetail.description: Indicate the alcohol shipment details. This object is mandatory if alcohol special service is selected.

accessibility.description:
Indicate the Dangerous Goods Accessibility Type.
Inaccessible means it does not have to be accessible on the aircraft. Accessible means it must be fully accessible on the aircraft, and is more strictly controlled.

options.description:
Specify the special handling requested for the package.
Example: BATTERY

containers.description: Indicate one or more containers used to pack dangerous goods commodities.

regulation.description: The hazardous package shipment regulation type.

DangerousGoodsDetail.description: Use this object to specify Dangerous Goods shipment Detail.

offeror.description: Specify the shipper name(offeror) or contact number. Required on all shipping papers.

hazardousCommodities.description: Specify the kinds and quantities of all hazardous commodities in the current container.

radioactiveContainerClass.description: Indicate the packaging type of the container used to package the radioactive materials.

innerReceptacles.description: Specifies the inner receptacles within the container.

HazardousCommodityContent.description: Documents the kind and quantity of an individual hazardous commodity in a package.

quantityType.description: Specifies type of a quantity unit.

HazardousCommodityInnerReceptacleDetail.description: This describes information about the inner receptacles for the hazardous commodity in a particular dangerous goods container.

labelTextOption.description: Specifies how the customer wishes the label text to be handled for this commodity in this package.

customerSuppliedLabelText.description: Text used in labeling the commodity under control of the labelTextOption field.

HazardousCommodityOptionDetail.description: Customer-provided specifications for handling individual commodities.

sequenceNumber.description: In conjunction with the regulatory identifier, this field uniquely identifies a specific hazardous materials commodity.

processingOptions.description: Indicates any special processing options to be applied to the description of the dangerous goods commodity.

subsidiaryClasses.description: Specifies the hazardous material subsidiary classes.

labelText.description: Specifies the DOT diamond hazard label type. This element can also include limited quantity or exemption number.

technicalName.description: Specify the technical name for the hazardous commodity.

authorization.description: Information related to quantity limitations and operator or state variations as may be applicable to the dangerous goods commodity.

reportableQuantity.description: The element specifies the reportable quantity of the hazardous material.

id.description: Specifies the ID of label text.

packingGroup.description: Identifies IATA packing group for a hazardous commodity.

properShippingName.description:
The proper shipping name as defined by the regulation.
The name can also include qualifying words.

HazardousCommodityDescription.description: Identifies and describes an individual hazardous commodity.

packingInstructions.description: Indicates the coded specification for how commodity is to be packed.

cargoAircraftOnly.description: Indicates the shipment is packaged/documented for movement ONLY on cargo aircraft.

HazardousCommodityPackingDetail.description: Specifies documentation and limits for validation of an individual packing group/category.

countryCode.description:
The two-letter code used to identify a country.
Example: US

localNumber.description: Telephone number to use for contact in the event of an emergency.

PhoneNumber.description: Indicates the telephone number to use for contact in the event of an emergency.

count.description: Indicate the number and type of packaging units for dangerous goods.

units.description: Specify the unit of the package.

HazardousCommodityPackagingDetail.description: Identifies number and type of packaging units for hazardous commodities.

codCollectionType.description:
Indicate the type of funds FedEx should collect upon shipment delivery.
Conditionally required for Ground COD rates

PackageCODDetail.description: Indicates package COD Detail.  COD main information is set in shipment level.

material.description: Describes the material composition of the battery or cell. Example: LITHIUM_METAL

regulatorySubType.description: Specify the regulation specific classification for the battery or cell.

packing.description: Indicate the packing arrangement of the battery or cell with respect to other items within the same package. Example: CONTAINED_IN_EQUIPMENT

BatteryClassificationDetail.description: Describe the attributes of a battery or cell that are used for classification purposes. Typically this structure would be used to allow customers to declare batteries or cells for which full dangerous goods documentation and procedures are not required.

Party_2.description: Indicate the party to a transaction including the physical address, contact information and account number information.

personName.description:
Specify contact name.
Note: Recommended Length is 70. There's no specific validation for the length.
Example: John Taylor

emailAddress.description:
Specify contact email address. Maximum length is 80.
Example: sample@company.com

phoneNumber.description:
Specify contact phone number. Maximum length is 15.
Example: 1234567890

phoneExtension.description:
Specify contact phone extension. Maximum length is 6.
Example: 1234

faxNumber.description:
Specify contact fax number. Maximum length is 15.
Example: 1234567890

companyName.description: Specify contact company name. Maximum length is 35.

RequestedShipmentSpecialServicesRequeste.description:
Specify the special services requested at the shipment level.
This has to be specified if rate data needed for the special services.

specialServiceTypes.description:
Indicate special services for which the rate data is being requested. Special Services are available at the shipment level for some or all service types.
Example: BROKER_SELECT_OPTION
Click here to see Shipment level Special Service Types

ShipmentSpecialServicesRequested.description:
Indicate special services for which the rate data is being requested. Special Services are available at the shipment level for some or all service types.
Example: [BROKER_SELECT_OPTION]
Click here to see Shipment level Special Service Types

DeliveryOnInvoiceAcceptanceDetail.description: Indicate the Delivery On Invoice Acceptance detail. Recipient is required for Delivery On Invoice Special service.

licenseOrExemptionNumber.description:
The export or license number for the ITAR shipment.
Example: 9871234

InternationalTrafficInArmsRegulationsDet.description: These are International Traffic In Arms Regulations shipment service Details.

options.description:
These are Pending Shipment processing options.
Example: ["ALLOW_MODIFICATIONS"]

PendingShipmentProcessingOptionsRequeste.description: Use this object to specify the processing options associated with Pending Shipment request. This is useful for the Email Label originator to specify if the completer can make modifications to editable shipment data.

RecommendedDocumentSpecification.description: These are recommended document specification which are recommended to be included with the shipment.

recipients.description: Describes specific information about the list of email label shipment reipients.

message.description: customer specified message to be included in the email to the end-user.

EmailLabelDetail.description:
Describes specific information about the email label shipment.
  • Message: Content of the email message
  • Recipients: EMailRecipient
  • emailAddress - email address of the recipient
  • role - role type of the recipient
  • optionsRequested
  • localization

emailAddress.description: This is the placeholder for Email address of the end-user to be  notified of the return label. Maximum length is 200 characters.

role.description: Specifies the role of the recipient to the pending shipment.

EmailRecipient.description: Use this object to specify the recipient email information.

EmailOptionsRequested.description: Indicates how the email notifications for the pending shipment need to be processed.

country.description:
This is country code.
Example: US
Click here to see Country Codes

language.description:
This is language code.
Example: en
Click here to see Locale

Locale.description:
These are Locale details.
Note: If the locale is left blank or an invalid locale is entered, an error message is returned in response.

documentType.description: These are the type of document specified in the PendingShipment request.

description.description: Indicate description of the shipping documents produced for the shipper by FedEx (see ShippingDocumentSpecification) which should be copied back to the shipper in the shipment result data.

documentId.description: Specify the document ID for the uploaded document.

UploadDocumentReferenceDetail.description: Upload document details provided by the initator of the shipment.

ShipmentDryIceDetail.description: Use this object to indicate package count with weight for this shipment containing dry ice. Dry ice is supported in both shipment level and package level services.

locationId.description:
This is an alphanumeric identifier used for Location/Facility Identification.

Example: YBZA

Note:
  • For HAL Shipment, Location ID is REQUIRED to ensure packages are delivered to the right location.
  • Use endpoint [Find Location] in [Location Search API], to find the correct location ID for your shipment.

locationType.description:
Specify the Location Type.
Example: FEDEX_ONSITE

HoldAtLocationDetail.description:
Use this object to specify required information for a shipment to be held at destination FedEx location.

Note: This object HoldAtLocationDetail is REQUIRED, when HOLD_AT_LOCATION is chosen in the specialServiceTypes.

ContactAndAddress.description: Specify the contact and address details of a location.

city.description:
Specify name of city, town, etc.
Example: Beverly Hills

stateOrProvinceCode.description:
Specify State or province code. Maximum length is 2.State code is required for US, CA, PR and not required for other countries. Conditional. Max length is 2.
Example: CA
Click here to see State Or Province Codes

postalCode.description:
Specify the postal code. This is optional for non postal- aware countries. Maximum length is 10.
Example: 65247
Click here to see Postal aware countries

countryCode.description:
The two-letter country code. Maximum length is 2.
Example: US
Click here to see Country Codes

residential.description: Indicate whether this address is residential (as opposed to commercial).

Address_1.description: This is detailed information on physical location. May be used as an actual physical address (place to which one could go), or as a container of address parts which should be handled as a unit (such as a city-state-ZIP combination within the US). Country code is required. Postal code is required for postal aware countries. State or province code is mandatory for Puerto Rico.

ShipmentSpecialServicesRequestedShipment.description: Use this object to specify Collect On Delivery (COD) shipment details.

remitToName.description:
Specifies the name of person or company receiving the secured or unsecured payment.
Example: FedEx

codCollectionType.description: Indicate the type of funds FedEx should collect upon shipment delivery.

returnReferenceIndicatorType.description: Indicate the type of reference information to include on the COD return shipping label.

rateLevelType.description: Specify whether the rate applied on bundle or indiividual package.

chargeLevelType.description: Specify whether the charges applied on current or all packages.

CODTransportationChargesDetail.description: These are COD Transportation Charges Detail.

type.description:
Indicate International Controlled Export Type.
Example: WAREHOUSE_WITHDRAWAL

InternationalControlledExportDetail.description: Use this object to specify International Controlled Export shipment Details.

shipTimestamp.description:
This is shipment date. Both the date and time portions of the string are expected to be used. The date should not be a past date or a date more than 10 days in the future. The time is the local time of the shipment based on the shipper's time zone.
Formats: YYYY-MM-DD, YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
Example: 2024-06-14 19:23:51

homedeliveryPremiumType.description: This is Home Delivery Premium Type. It allows to specify additional premimum service options for the home delivery shipment. Can specify Evening delivery or a Date certain, or can specify appointment for the delivery.

HomeDeliveryPremiumDetail.description: These are Special service elements for FedEx Ground Home Delivery shipments. If selected, element homedeliveryPremiumType is mandatory.

RequestedShipmentCustomsClearanceDetail.description: This is Customs clearance data associated with the shipment. This is used for both international and intra-country shipping and rating. Customs commodity data is required for international and intra-country rating.

brokers.description:
Conditional.
Required if BROKER_SELECT_OPTION is specified as a shipment special service type. A country code must be specified in addition to one of the following address items: postal code, city, or location id.

freightOnValue.description: Indicates Freight on value for customs.

commodities.description: Indicates the details about the dutiable packages. Maximum upto 999 commodities per shipment.

CustomsClearanceDetail.description: This is Customs clearance data, used for both international and intra-country shipping and rating. Customs commodity data is required for international and intra-country rating.

shipmentPurpose.description: The reason for the shipment.  Note: SOLD is not a valid purpose for a Proforma Invoice.

CommercialInvoice.description:
The Commercial Invoice element is required for electronic upload of CI data. It will serve to create/transmit an electronic Commercial Invoice through the FedEx system.
Customers are responsible for printing their own Commercial Invoice.
If you would like FedEx to generate a Commercial Invoice and transmit it to Customs for clearance purposes, you need to specify that in the 'ETDDetail/RequesteDocumentCopies' element.
Support consists of a Maximum of 99 commodity line items.

paymentType.description: Indicate the payment Type. Applicable for Express and Ground rates.

Payment.description: These are details about shipment payment. Value payor is optional when paymentType provided as SENDER.

responsibleParty.description: These are payer details such as address, account and contacts.

Payor.description:
This is payer Information responsible for paying for the shipment.
Note: Optional when paymentType is SENDER.

accountNumber.value:
This is the account number. Maximum Length is 9.
Example: Your account number

description.description:
Indicate the description of the dutiable packages.
Maximum Length is 450.

weight.description: Specify the Total weight of this commodity. This element is used to estimate duties and taxes.

quantity.description:
Specify the total number of units (using quantityUnits as the unit of measure) of this commodity present in the shipment. This element is used to estimate duties and taxes.
Example: 1

customsValue.description: Specify the required Customs value for this commodity.

allOf.description: Specifies the unit price of the commodity.

numberOfPieces.description:
Specifies the number of pieces for this commodity.
Example: 10

countryOfManufacture.description:
This is commodity country of manufacture. This is required. Maximum allowed length is 4.
Example: US
Click here to see Country Codes

quantityUnits.description:
Indicate quantiy unit used. Used to estimate duties and taxes
Example: PCS
click here to see Commodity Unit Measures

harmonizedCode.description:
This is to specify the Harmonized Tariff System (HTS) code to meet U.S. and foreign governments' customs requirements. These are mainly used to estimate the duties and taxes.
Example: A six digit code for Almonds fresh or dried is 080211. The HTS code for pistachios in shell is 080251. The HTS code for fish is HS203.
To research the classification for your commodity, use the FedEx Global Trade Manager online at fedex.com/gtm. You can find the commodities and its respective codes by logging into FedEx and selecting harmonized code option. You will find country-specific information to determine whether your commodity is considered to be a document or non-document for your destination.
For additional information about harmonized code, refer to harmonized code.

partNumber.description: Specify the part number if any. Example: P1

carrierCode.description: Identifies which carrier is being described.

description.description: Description

RequestedShipmentSmartPostInfoDetail.description: Indicate the FedEx Smartpost shipment details. Required for Smartpost shipments only.

ancillaryEndorsement.description:
Indicate the type of ancillary endorsement. Is required for Presorted Standard but not for returns or parcel select. Note not all are usable for all ancillary endorsements.
For more information, refer to the FedEx SmartPost®.

hubId.description:
Specify the four-digit numeric Hub ID value used during rate quote for smartport shipments.
Click here to see Hub Ids

indicia.description:
Specify the indicia type.
Available options include:
  • MEDIA_MAIL
  • PARCEL_SELECT (1 LB through 70 LB)
  • PRESORTED_BOUND_PRINTED_MATTER
  • PRESORTED_STANDARD (less than 1 LB)
  • PARCEL_RETURN

specialServices.description:
Specify the special handling associated with Smartpost Shipment.
Click here to see Shipment Level Special Service Types

SmartPostInfoDetail.description:
Use this object to specify the smartpost shipment details.
Required for SMARTPOST service. If SmartPostInfoDetail is indicated, the elements below it are also required.

returnType.description: The type of return shipment being requested.

streetLines.description:
This is the combination of number, street name, etc.
Note: At least one line is required and streetlines more than 3 will be ignored. Empty lines should not be included. Maximum Length per line is 35.
Example: [10 FedEx Parkway, Suite 302, .etc.]

countryCode.description:
The two-letter country code.
Maximum length is 2.
Example: US
Click here to see Country Codes

name.description:
The localized name of the tax.
Example: Denmark VAT

description.description:
The description of the Surcharge/Tax.
Example: Denmark VAT

type.description:
The type of Surcharge/Tax.
Example: VAT

companyName.description: This is a placeholder for company name. Maximum length is 35.

faxNumber.description: This is a placeholder for Fax number. Maximum length is 15.

personName.description: This is a placeholder for contact person's name. Maximum Length is 70.

phoneNumber.description: This is a placeholder for phone number associated with this contact. Maximum length is 15.
